The paper introduces an algebra for modelling states of computations involving dynamic data structures, which suggests it belongs to the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also mentions a term rewriting system with rule priorities, which is a common technique in automated theorem proving and logic (cs.LO) sub-category. The use of data structures and state changes also suggests it could belong to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper also mentions an upgrade to molecular dynamics, which could suggest it belongs to the scientific computing (cs.SC) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses features to reclaim garbage, which suggests it could belong to the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
